Program: Outlook
Title: 06/03/2012
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p00p5qvt
Last Broadcast Date: Wed 7 Mar 2012
Extraordinary personal stories from around the world. Today, Irene Villa, who lost both legs in a Madrid bomb attack in 1991, tells us how she's stayed optimistic. Also, Dame Daphne Sheldrick on a lifetime of working with elephants and other wild animals in Kenya. Her book is called An African Love Story: Love, Life and Elephant'. And 74-year-old Bangladeshi Jharna Dhara Choudhury on how Mahatma Gandhi inspired her commitment to education and community work. Show less